resolution: "Allowed non-owner audit evidence appends through pm update --allow-audit-update for comments, files, and docs only."
expected_result: "Agents can append audit comments and linked file/doc evidence in one audited update without claiming another owner's item, while unsafe mutation classes stay blocked."
actual_result: Focused and full coverage regression tests verify allowed evidence appends plus blocked unsafe audit-update fields; temp project smoke confirmed CLI behavior.
comments[6]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-06-13T20:59:27.028Z",claude-code-agent,"DEFERRED (design tension): GH-207 was already deliberately addressed (code comment 'GH-207' in update.ts) — append-style --comment/--file/--doc are intentionally routed through dedicated commands (pm comments --allow-audit-comment, pm files --force) with exact retry guidance in the audit-scope error. Reversing that to permit inline non-owner appends under --allow-audit-update changes a documented decision and the audit-scope security story. Keeping restricted; the retry guidance already gives a one-paste path. Revisit only with explicit maintainer sign-off."
  "2026-06-18T23:28:25.039Z",codex-implementation,"Evidence update: focused unit test passed (95 tests); build/contracts/docs-links/changelog/security checks passed; temp-dir smoke verified non-owner --allow-audit-update appends comment/file/doc and still rejects --test; dependency sweep found commander 15 latest but skipped because it requires Node >=22.12 while package engines remain >=20; Auto Release push-race failure maps to closed pm-5oti and current main has retry/rebase helper with latest manual Auto Release green."
  "2026-06-18T23:29:44.632Z",codex-implementation,"Coverage follow-up: first full coverage run failed only because the removed --comment restriction left replacement-map branches for --file/--doc uncovered in update.ts; added focused helper assertions for those replacement commands and rerunning focused tests plus coverage."
  "2026-06-18T23:35:41.712Z",codex-implementation,"Final local verification: focused update suite passed (95 tests); full coverage passed 228 files / 4609 tests with 100% statements, branches, functions, and lines; typecheck, static quality, docs-skills, docs-links, version check, contracts check, changelog check, security scan, audit, package doctor, telemetry status, Sentry 24h unresolved query, and temp-dir GH-207 smoke passed or were clean. Existing validate resolution warnings are backlog-wide and history drift is ok."
  "2026-06-18T23:45:01.972Z",codex-implementation,"Review follow-up: addressed CodeRabbit findings by forcing audit-update comment authors to the actual command author, updating audit-scope error guidance to mention allowed evidence appends, and clarifying replacement-map intent for narrower audit scopes."
  "2026-06-18T23:51:35.638Z",codex-implementation,"Review follow-up verification: focused update-command test passed (95 tests), full coverage passed 228 files / 4609 tests with 100% statements, branches, functions, and lines, changelog:pm:check passed unchanged, and pm validate history drift remained ok with only existing backlog-wide resolution warnings."
